    <h1>Arty Na&#xAD;tional Day</h1>
    <h2>With Na&#xAD;tional Day around the cor&#xAD;ner, arts in&#xAD;sti&#xAD;tu&#xAD;tions are pulling out all the stops to cel&#xAD;e&#xAD;brate in style</h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200804/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-04"><time>2020-08-04</time></a>
        - <span>FRONT PAGE</span>
        - <span role="byline">Ong Sor Fern Se&#xAD;nior Cul&#xAD;ture Cor&#xAD;re&#xAD;spon&#xAD;dent sor&#xAD;fern@sph.com.sg</span>
    </section>

    <p>Au­gust is a month to paint the town red – 10 build­ings in the civic district will be lit in scar­let for Na­tional Day cel­e­bra­tions.</p>
    <p>Th­ese in­clude mu­se­ums as well as her­itage sites such as the Cen­tral Fire Sta­tion, the Ar­me­nian Church and Chi­jmes.</p>
    <p>So­cial dis­tanc­ing and ca­pac­ity caps are in place at her­itage in­sti­tu­tions, but there are plenty of Na­tional Day fes­tiv­i­ties to look out for, both in real life and on­line.</p>
    <p>The Na­tional Mu­seum of Sin­ga­pore, Asian Civil­i­sa­tions Mu­seum, In­dian Her­itage Cen­tre, Malay Her­itage Cen­tre and Sun Yat Sen Nanyang Memo­rial Hall will have Open Houses this week­end and visi­tors can col­lect their NDP 2020 SG To­gether Packs at th­ese places.</p>
    <p>Here are some of the most in­ter­est­ing arts, cul­ture and her­itage pro­grammes to check out for the com­ing long week­end.</p>

